{{Quote|Not because the jungle kills you. You get it? Just because it is what it is. The Jungle doesn't do anything. It's just a place. It's a place where many, many things live&hellip;and all of them die. Fantasizing about it&mdash;pretending it's something it's not&mdash;is fatal. That's your free life lesson for the day, keep it in mind.|[[Nick Rostu]]|<ref name="Shatterpoint (novel)">[[Shatterpoint (novel)|''Shatterpoint'']]</ref>}}
On the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Haruun Kal/Legends|Haruun Kal]], the '''[[Korunnal Highland]]''' was a continent-sized plateau that was the only habitable area of the planet, as it was the only area that sat high enough above the toxic [[cloudsea]] that encapsulated most of the lowlands to support life. Except for [[Pelek Baw/Legends|Pelek Baw]], the capital of Haruun Kal, the entire plateau was covered by dense, deadly jungle.

